reviews:
My daughter and I loved it here - location great really nice area in 8th and around a mile to Arc De Triophme mile and half to Eiffel Tower - restaurants nearby - shops Galleries Layfayette walkable 1 km
Lovely room great beds & soundproofing , modern bathroom , nice leisure centre with pool
We are really glad we chose this hotel it was small & boutique staff were wonderful Loved it all

Beautiful stay in a great hotel with the family in the most beautiful city of France, right in the heart of the city. Family of 2 adults and 2 kids - Superior suite with great view. Spacious room, very clean appartment.

I loved this hotel, first of all because it's very central, yet very quiet, both my husband and I are light sleepers , yet this hotel was completely quiet, no noise from the street, or the corridors. The room had a bathtub and there is a heater pool downstairs which is open until 10PM, we used it every day, because it was open late and also it was very nice and not crowded at all. Concierge also very accommodating with us. All in all, really only positives.

The hotel is ideally located to major tourist attractions. The hotel staff is nice and accommodating. The rooms are smaller than I imagined. I do not think it’s ideal for 2 people. The drink and restaurant/room service menu is limited, but service and food was good. My stay at this hotel was fine.

We spent 3 nights at the hotel during the Easter period. The room is cosy, the bed and pillow were comfortable. The hotel is beautiful, from the reception, to the pool and the room the design is clever and pleasant to the eye. We had a cancelled flight and we could only get to Paris the next day and they refunded the first night. We got a room on the 4th floor with a beautiful view over the boulevard from the balcony. The toiletries are Lalique, very nice and pleasant. For my wife's birthday we got 2 glasses of champagne, that was a nice touch! The best thing is the soundproofing, there's no noise coming from the boulevard. That is very impressive! The only minor negative is that the rooms are on the smaller size (similar to other Parisian hotels).

All PERFECT amenities , food , pool , gym
Staff SUPER and ready to help at anytime with a smile
Breakfast nice and the Hotel bed and. Clean was superb
We will visiting soon since we loe Paris and the Hotel

I recently stayed at Villa Haussmann during Paris Fashion Week. The hotel was an oasis of calm in this busy period!
The rooms, and particularly the beds, are very comfortable. Our room was always clean and tidy with room service and the added extra of White Company toiletries in the bathroom was lovely.
All of the staff were very friendly and our main point of contact, Skander, was brilliant. They really can’t do enough for you and a taxi is ready at a moment’s notice!
An all- round great experience and I look forward to staying there again soon.

The only thing that spoiled our stay was the breakfast. We were there on a Thursday & Friday night. They run out of items from the buffet including cereals and milk. The pastries were a bit stale on the Friday morning but fresher on Saturday. There was no milk to have with the cereals they did have on Saturday. The staff seemed to be not bothered - this was something that happened. If you’re paying €35 for breakfast as some people were you expect better - especially in the centre of Paris with many supermarkets and bakeries in short walking distance. This is totally unacceptable

Brief(ish) but fair review for this hotel!

Hotel - Absolutely spot on design wise. The majority of staff are awesome with a few speaking English, yes some are a little funny with you but it is what it is.

Hotel location - the district the hotel is located in is very popular! Within a few minutes walk has everything you could need.

Hotel issues - I am not a person who goes looking for problems however, when you are staying in the best room in the house and having spent £600 per night (for two night - £1200 total) you don’t expect small completely unavoidable issues. I would rather have to deal with a big issue that aren’t the hotels fault as opposed to minor issues that are avoidable, frankly they are just disappointing. The first morning we decided to get room service - I completed the form the night before and placed it outside my door. The next morning breakfast came and it was wrong, it was wrong and they actually forgot my wife’s entire selection - awesome thanks!!! Next issue - and for me this is worst than getting the food wrong, I went to the mini bar to grab a snack and I noticed the jelly sweat pot had a loose cap on it, after inspecting it I could see someone (I can just assume the previous guest) had opened it and ate half the sweets. Whilst this sounds like a little issue, this worries me because what else has been messed with by some unknown person, again this is something you wouldn’t expect when you are paying £600 a night. I reported both my issues to reception and was told the manager would be in touch (he/she hadn’t) - upon checkout the girl (who was super sweet and polite) asked how my stay was - I informed her of my issues and she was so disappointed. She offered to cover my bar bill €13 euros, my mini bar bill = the water, the can of coke, nuts and a packet of crisps = total €17 - total offered for comp was €30 - I declined. She was shocked and I said I didn’t complain to get something free - I’m sorry but when I pay £600 a night I don’t want issues. The hotel should know best and for me this has left a really sour taste in my mouth - human error / lazy / careless attitude is to blame for both these issues and I hope they learn by these mistakes and this review.

Very good upmarket hotel and area, near to all the sights. Hotel is small luxury boutique with compact rooms but very nicely decorated. Some rooms on the upper floors have a view of the Eiffel Tower as well. Staff are very professional, friendly and helpful. The rooms have tea/coffee facilities and a well stocked mini bar and comfortable beds with large tv. Swimming pool is heated and relaxing and not crowded especially in the mornings. Did not try their breakfast, But the bar looks out to the street and is comfortable. Good base to see all the sights with low taxi costs. Overall very good choice for a weekend in Paris and for sightseeing.

I stayed at the Villa Haussman recently with my son who has special needs. Patrick at the front desk was outstanding and so caring. The room was very good, beds were very comfortable, the AC was outstanding, the shower pressure was great, bathroom was beautiful. Great location and very quiet. Very clean and nicely decorated. Front desk were always kind and friendly, outgoing. I left a day early for a Hurricane that was coming to my home and they refunded me on my last night even though I am sure they didn't need to as per their booking policy. I would stay there again at my next visit to Paris. Thank-you again Villa Haussman! Until we meet again.

Overall excellent one night stay as a tourist in Paris. Hotel is centrally located on Boulevard Haussmann and in short walking distance to Printemps and Gallery Lafayette. A Metro station is just around the corner. Rooms are on tge small side but nicely decorated and well kept. The sound proof windows and doors are among the best I have experienced. Even with a direct view of the busy cobblestoned Boulevard Haussmann it was complete (!) silent in the room. Staff was very friendly and attentive. I will definitely come back. Highly recommend.

We stayed at the Villa Haussman for our summer break during August 2022 for 8 nights in total. The hotel experience was absolutely amazing and from the moment we checked in, we could see the superior customer service from all of the staff. We stayed in 2 adjoining rooms which were at the end of the corridor so they could be opened up and joined fully and this proved to be a wonderful setup for us and our 2 kids.
The rooms were spacious and very comfortable. Even though you are at the center of a busy road, there is no noise coming through and you are able to get a very good and sound sleep during the night. The hotel location is perfect as every major attraction in Paris is easy to get to and there are really good rail links very close by.
The food in the hotel is absolutely wonderful and we had breakfast here everyday where we found several options catering to any type of need. The staff are also very helpful in recommending nearby options if you are interested in trying something outside.
The attentiveness and care the staff showed at all times, especially to our kids was brilliant and made us feel right at home.
This is a great hotel for a stay in Paris and definitely on our visit again list.

The quality of furnishings, room layout and bed linen all made this room feel special (deluxe).

The attention to detail and our need by the staff was second to none and we felt special throughout- we were definitely welcome.

We will definitely be back.

Michael and Sander were amazing! La Villa Haussmann is an amazing hotel in Paris, actually the absolute best I’ve stayed at in Paris in my past 5 visits.

Traveling for the first time with my 8 year old & 30 year old brother. La Villa Haussmann is centrally located and had a great pool (oversized hot tub with excellent multiple jets) perfect for an 8 year old daughter who wants to wade around the water or for adults wanted to rest achy feet from exploring. Rooms were spacious and sooo modern and had gorgeous views on the 6th floor. Even a lovely view of the Eiffel Tower. Michael, Sander & the evening team were so accommodating - they all deserve raises 🙌.

We stayed here for our 20th anniversary in 2017 and returned for our 25th. Perfect location, price and an amazing staff and room quality. Easy access to any part of Paris via the Metro (several near-by stations) and from there any of the train stations and airports.

We stayed here for 5 nights in May with our 12 year old daughter and I honestly don’t think we could have picked a better hotel. The location was perfect, 8 mins walk to the Champs Elysee, 5 mins walk to the Opera House and 2 mins for the subway. Some nice bars and restaurants nearby that serve late if arriving late like we did. The style and decor of the hotel is very chic but it was the staff that made this trip so memorable, they honestly couldn’t have been more welcoming and helpful. Nothing was too much trouble and everything was with a smile. It made such a difference. The pool was fabulous and so welcoming after a day walking the city. We had a suite on the 6th floor with a view of the Eiffel Tower. It was amazing. Very stylish, quite spacious with everything you might need. I would definitely recommend this hotel and if the pop arises, I will definitely return.

Great service from every member of staff very helpful professional polite and very welcoming, good location, clean stylish rooms, fabulous spa area we will be returning for sure and would highly recommend.

Superb hotel on Boulevard Haussmann. Very classy and brilliant location near all the major attractions . The staff are amazing. Breakfast is fantastic. The rooms are on the small side but that’s Paris for you. They are beautifully decorated

We have visited Paris for the first time and what a great experience !!! Villa Haussemann contributed a lot for our lovely stay. Hotel staff were very professional, helpfull and no small thing is too much to ask. We have stayed 4 nights, breakfast included. Very chill and relax atmosphere at the breakfast restaurant downstairs. Lovely corner room with two balconies, clean and always tidy ! X comfortable beds like you are on cloud nine ! 100% will come back . Reception staff very helpful to hold our luggage after checkout so we could go shopping before our travel outbound. Thank everyone at Villa Housemann !

We enjoyed our stay at this hotel! The rooms are small but are very clean and well kept up. The hotel staff was friendly and always greeted us as we were coming and going. The hotel breakfast was perfect for starting off the day. On the whole, a very nice hotel and good experience!

The only slight downside to this hotel is the location. While it’s very central, it didn’t offer much walkability to major attractions. You will need to take a cab most places to avoid a long walk.

Finest staff of any hotel I’ve stayed in many years! From the desk staff and waiters to the manager himself, these kind folks could not have been more helpful and accommodating every hour of the day and night. Knew where to steer us, called ahead for reservations, fixed emergencies, and accommodated our every request.

The food was excellent, wait staff attentive and swift. Hotel is centrally located close to Champs Elysees, shopping, and Metro. Nicely appointed, and the facilities are great - spa and indoor pool to boot.

Only drawback…rooms are tight, but that’s the way it is in most of Paris, friends. Unless you stay at you stay at the Crillon, don’t expect a huge sweet. But this hotel does have larger suites at higher rates.

Altogether a wonderful experience and in my many upcoming trips to Paris I’ll be staying right here.

I visited Paris together with my daughter and it was a great experience, especially for her first visit in Paris. The hotel is located perfectly to visit all interesting hot spots in Paris even by walking. The service at the hotel is outstanding, rooms are very clean, well designed and very cozy. Breakfast was excellent and Spa wonderful. it was a great experience! Merci beaucoup La Villa Haussmann!

this hotel has a very high standard, the personnel is very friendly and competent, room with view on Eiffel Tower is magnificent, nice room with lot of space, nice swimming pool per couple for 20min during Covid, roomservice and breakfast is excellent !

La Villa Haussmann is a wonderful hotel in a fantastic location. The hotel is beautifully decorated and the rooms are very comfortable. A special thanks to Florian who paid attentive care to our needs while at the hotel. Thank you.

Clean hotel but room was quite small. White modern bathroom and spacious shower. Gorgeous foyer and restaurant downstairs which we didnt eat at as it was expensive. About a 10 to 15 minute walk to the champs elysee. Can walk to all sites of attraction. Lacks good resturants around it but the bakery across the road became our go to for breakfast. Hard to find well priced restaurants in Paris in general. Close to gallerie lafayettes if you enjoy shopping. Streets are a bit dark at night and can sometimes feel unsafe. Good thing that its away from the hustle bustle but also may want to be closer to the tourist areas.

We got a corner suite, so that was fine. The hotel has a pool but a bit depressing down there as it is too dark. The restaurant was only okay and the service is below what you would expect. Not a bad stay but wouldn't go back. Stayed July 2018.

Our hotel stay was booked months in advance for my wife's birthday. Two days prior to our stay I contacted the hotel because of the upcoming strike that would shut down the airport in Paris we were flying into from the US. They assured me if our flight was cancelled due to the strike and airport shutting down we would be able to cancel our stay and get a full refund. I told the person i spoke with that I was outside the 48 hour window to cancel but if I waited for my flight to be cancelled it would not. He assured me because of the crazy extenuating circumstances it would not be a problem. I waited and the day of our trip the flight was cancelled. I contacted the hotel and they told me we would not be refunded because it was inside 48 hours. I told them the situation and what I was told 2 days prior but they denied my request. Long story short, everyone I have spoken with at the hotel, everyday for the last 10 days has been very rude. I have asked to speak with the general manager every day I call and they tell me every day he will be in tomorrow and will call you back. Still NOTHING!!! Today I was told I could not talk to him because it wasn't his problem. She also told me she couldn't talk anymore because she had other customers to help. I was shocked! I would love a full refund but today I even asked for a stay in the future or to just pay for the first nights stay because I notified them we would not be coming. All denied.
I travel a ton for work and for pleasure and have never given a negative review. After speaking with friends I know who have lived in Paris or stayed there have all said they are not surprised with the customer service I have received from this particular hotel. It's apparently a decent place to stay but when it comes to the employees caring about their customers, they could care less!
I refuse to give up so if anyone has any suggestions on how to help that would be great! We are currently out $1,000 still!!

My wife and I were planning on coming back next year to Paris but I can guarantee we will not be staying here!!

We stayed 2 nights for my wife's birthday, and from the second we arrived until departure it was an immensely enjoyable experience. The hotel is extremely clean and rooms really comfortable. We had a corner room facing onto the main boulevard, with windows on both sides. However once the windows were closed, you couldnt hear any traffic. Leaving them open in the morning to hear Paris waking up was a treat!
The location of the hotel is an easy 10 min walk to the Arc de Triomphe, and the Champs-Élysées. And if you want to stretch the legs, 40 mins will take you to Montmartre and the Seine.
We were treated to a glass of bubbly during our stay, and we also took advantage of the basement pool after a walk.
Id also like to add that all the staff were extremely helpful and courteous, and made us feel very welcome. In particular Jonathon who was exceptional, always greeted us with a smile and is a credit to his profession.
We would definitely return here in future.

We stayed at La Villa Haussmann for one week in a Junior Suite, and overall felt it was a nice little boutique hotel. We had initially booked a Deluxe Room but after reading from several other reviewers about how small the rooms were, we upgraded to a Junior Suite and were very glad we did as even the actual size of the Jr Suite was a bit smaller than how they look in the pictures on the hotel website. Keep in mind though we are coming from Los Angeles where we have very spacious hotel rooms, but all in all the Junior Suite was very well suited for our needs, and even had 2 really nice large windows you could open up and stand out on very small balconies where you could see the Eiffel Tower. As others have noted, these windows are also super sound proof where once closed you wont hear a peep from outside. The bathroom was a nice size with a rainfall shower and even a stand alone tub. Overall though, if you're coming from the states, do yourself a favor and grab a junior suite. The location of the hotel was nice but does get pretty quiet on the weekends. There was a nice little bakery across the street where we grabbed coffee and croissants every morning. A couple blocks up the streets were 2 small bustling cafes (St Augustin and Le Pepeniere) where we sat and people watched and had some wine a couple nights. Keep in mind though, pretty much all restaurants close around 10pm in paris, so if you're used to late night eating, youll need to adjust your eating times. La Pepeniere though does stay open a bit later. The metro also was one block away and we used it pretty much everyday with no problems getting anywhere in the city. We also used Uber a few times when we got a bit dressed up, and it was just as easy as using it in the states. The front desk was also super friendly, spoke wonderful english, and always helped us with any questions we had. We never ate at the hotel, but ordered room service the first night as we were super tired. While the room service says its open 24hours, once it becomes later into the night, it looks like they dont have everything in stock as they had to change a few of our dishes based on what they had at the moment, and also did not have many of the desserts avaiable. Overall though, if you're looking for a nice little boutique hotel in Paris, with nicely designed and appointed rooms, close to the metro, and in a slightly quieter area of Paris (away from the touristy area), La Villa Haussmann is a great choice.

Really nice, well-maintained luxury hotel. Excellent location within a few minute walk to Metro. Buffet breakfast is expensive for what is offered; would opt for any pf the many neighborhood cafes. A/C unit did not work the first night but was fixed soon after
informing them.

Yes, Paris is lovely and wonderful, but our vacation was so value added by staying here! The attentiveness to all our requests was outstanding. Location was perfect! Near a Metro, walking distance to Champs Elysee and Arc de Triomphe, close to great restaurants and in a quiet neighborhood setting. Our room (family suite) had a wrap-around balcony and was very well appointed. Even could see the top tip of the Eiffel!
Will stay here again on vacation.

La Villa Haussmann is an excellent option of hotel in the 8eme in Paris. The rooms are new, clean, elegantly decorated. The staff is very polite and professional. The swimming pool is perfect and my daughter just loved it. The breakfest is also very good even though a little bit expensive. I highly recommend and will return on my next time in the city. The windows have sound isolation wich is perfect for that busy part of the city.

This was my boyfriend and I's first trip to Paris and this hotel made the trip even more memorable and enjoyable. It was the little touches that made the difference.
-they did their best to get us an early check-in as we were exhausted.
-they take all your bags upon arrival and then put them in your room when it is ready.
- the concierge took us into the elevator and walked us all the way to our room upon arrival.
-the room was clean, spacious, and comfortable (the classic room was very pleasant and not crammed like some reviews said. High ceilings, plenty of space for both of our suitcases. You do have to rearrange some furniture to open the window all the way but that was not a big deal).
-the room was sound proof and the bed was so comfortable. They offer three different kinds of pillows. I spilled hair products on the memory foam pillow I brought from home so I was relieved to see they provided the same kind.
-their was a personalized letter to welcome us with little lemon cakes when we walked in.
-the room temperature was adjustable and we were always comfortable.
-the curtains can completely block out any light, very cozy for sleeping but I recommend not closing the curtains. We were so comfortable our first night we slept in way later than we wanted!
-pool was so warm it was like a big hot tub. I loved it. The last day we stayed it was a few degrees cooler. Not sure why but it was actually a pleasant change as it was more comfortable to actually swim around in.
-we used the gym every morning. It is small but large enough for both my boyfriend and I to get a bit of exercise in before we start our day. Mostly cardio machines (fine by me!) and my boyfriend made due with the adjustable dumbbells. It's not a lot but enough for a vacation and quite workable.
-the cleaning staff were wonderful and worked around when my boyfriend and I were in and out of our room. They always kept all the shower products and teas well stocked.
-everyone was welcoming and I wouldn't change a thing.

The hotel is really well located in a fun neighborhood! There is a great little terrace just out front where they serve drinks and snacks. We waited for our room there.

The room itself was a bit small but very nice and well equipped. Very comfortable. We had a great view of the statue out front from our window.

Service was great as well. We had our small dog with us and they made her feel very welcomed! There is a small gym and pool. Breakfast, served buffet-style, was quite good as well.

If you’re looking for a hotel to stay in, that gives great service, that has excellent air-conditioning, and is moderately priced, this is the hotel for you. Me and my wife enjoyed it very much. When we call down for a request to the front desk, they responded within five minutes. They pride their selves in good service. Their rooms are very nice and clean. They have a nice spa, and a nice bar and restaurant. We would definitely return to this hotel.

DISASTER
We booked a 3 night stay to start off our European honeymoon and arrived around 1 PM local. Understandably the room was not ready for check-in since we were early so we went to explore the area.

We came back at 3PM as requested and the room still wasn't ready. There were 2 other parties waiting to check-in as well. After 30 minutes,I politely asked how we were doing & the front desk lady said 15 mins. More than 30 minutes passed and still not ready.

FINALLY around 430PM our room was ready and of course, the A/C DOES NOT WORK! This was never mentioned until I asked about it. The front desk said that the hotel is aware and the entire 1st floor had no A/C

Came back that evening to a room without A/C and it was SUPER HOT out. The front desk offered us a SMALL bucket of ice to perhaps cool the room down. Small as in maybe 50 ice cubes which melted in 10 mins

The next day, I asked for an update. They said that we would not have AC for Sunday night either and it maybe up on Monday. The hotel had no other rooms available

We cancelled the rest of the stay and went down the street to Maison Albar Hotel Opera Diamond. It's a 5 star hotel and was same in pricing.

No mention of a refund or at least some discount for staying. They KNEW that the room didn't have AC yet made us wait hours for checking in. The hotel should be upfront and honest when we first arrived. Give us the option to stay in a NO AC room or cancel.

Glad we left when we did and salvaged the rest of our trip.

La Villa Haussman is a lovely boutique hotel located in a quiet residential neighborhood. Walking distance to Galleries Lafayette and Printemps stores. My only comment is that all the surrounding cafes and bistros do not serve dinner after 10:00pm so if late night is your thing you are better off staying closer to Champs Elysee or other more commercial area. The rooms are small but very stylish. Hotel was quiet.

Visited here for the night whilst on a business trip - efficient check-in, pleasant staff, room reasonably spacious for Paris, and with good bathroom. Bed very comfortable, and room came with good size TV, nice coffee/tea making facilities etc. Very central and ideal location.

Just returned from a three night stay at this hotel in the centre of Paris and can’t recommend it enough! Pretty, central location, gorgeously appointed hotel (particularly comfy beds/bedding) lovely spa facilities with a very warm pool, nice food and lovely staff.
Would definitely stay here again if visiting Paris and would highly recommend it.
We stayed in room 601, a junior suite which was well appointed and reasonably spacious with a view of the Eiffel Tower

Everything from the staff, beds, bath, neighborhood, couldn't have been better. We booked 2 junior suites and they were perfect with two adults and a child per room. The rooms had views of the Eiffel Tower and the tree lined streets just added to the ambience of a wonderful stay. Wish we could have stayed longer.

One of the most comfortable hotel beds I’ve ever experienced. Everything about this hotel was clean and friendly (except that it seemed more complicated to get ice than I’d expected), but the bed itself was absolutely perfect. Highly recommend!

We transferred here after a 2-week tour that ended in Paris. The tour hotel was nice but too far away from the center of town and I’m familiar with this Arrondissement from when I lived in Paris many years ago. It was just perfect for us! Thanks to the efforts of Lea and Arnaud, our transition went very smoothly and we were able to check in early. The room was small—as expected in this area—but well appointed and we loved the doors that opened onto the balcony with fresh air and a view of the neighborhood. When closed, there was absolutely NO traffic noise. We appreciated the Nespresso machine and the electric kettle—very handy. The room was spotless,
comfortable, and very well maintained. The restaurant was closed most of our stay due to the holiday (Ascension) but we did eat there the first day and both the food and service were excellent. We also had a cheese plate delivered from room service which was very prompt and absolutely delicious, with generous portions that were plenty for two. There is also an excellent bakery across the street that is good for both breakfast and lunch, as well as a Monoprix within a short walking distance. The steam bath was awesome and we also very much enjoyed the indoor pool. Arnaud also arranged a private car for us to DeGaulle airport which was very affordable and convenient for an early morning flight. We couldn’t have been happier with our stay here and would return in a heartbeat! Highly recommended!

A wonderful hotel with very personal service. Loved the breakfast, set us up each day. The staff were friendly and helpful and the rooms very comfortable. The street epitomised Paris and the interior of the hotel was elegant and very French, no bland anywhere in the world feelings here. I will recommend this hotel to family and friends.

We have been to Paris a number of times. I have to say this hotel tops them all! The hotel it self is stunning! The staff and level of customer service are outstanding! We will definitely stay here again!’

We stayed here for 5 days and it was nothing but pure perfection!! We are at the restaurant for lunch and food was absolutely delicious! The staff was amazing and soooo friendly! I didn’t get the name of the guy who helped us during our entire stay but he had glasses, short brown curlyish hair, skinny. He was so helpful whenever we needed anything! Room service was great too as well as the layout of the room itself! I have nothing but good things to say about this hotel! Also train station near by so super convenient!

This hotel is brilliant. The staff are lovely and cannot do enough for you, even kind enough to book things for you or make reservations before I arrived.

The room service is spectacular and so well presented. I would recommend the Foie Gras. There are so many nice little touches by this hotel.

The pool and steam room are so modern and clean and great for a dip in the morning or after a day of walking around.

Big shout out to Arnaud and Heron, so lovely.

The breakfast was too expensive (although that’s Paris all over) so we didn’t get that. There is a lovely bakery across the street though with sensible prices.

La Villa Haussmann has an excellent location, walking distance to the Champs Elysees and the wonderful shopping areas as well as many excellent restaurants. The hotel common areas and the sleeping rooms are beautifully appointed and updated, very clean, inviting and comfortable. The pool and spa area is lovely; although we didn't use it, we did take a trip downstairs to have a peek. Breakfast is plentiful and delicious with lots of options - a real treat. The real stand out by far is the hotel staff; they are all without exception genuinely friendly, helpful, and all around delightful. They made our stay especially wonderful. Special thanks to Apolline for helping us to order our dinner through Deliveroo on the hotel computer the one night we wanted to stay in, and to Heron, who never failed to smile at our goofy jokes. We will definitely stay again!

Well renovated hotel, pleasant and doted of a beautiful SPA. Rooms are very fonctional but size will not allow to have an additional kid bed

Very pleasant staff, always at your disposal.

The restaurant is more a brasserie offering good meals

Great experience - would recommend

Not often moved to write a review. Villa Haussmann is the finest hotel I have ever stayed in. I have traveled all over the world and have paid 3x as much. Never stayed anywhere in the world that moved me to write. This is the place!!! Total home run!!!

Went to the monuments and wondered what it was like to be treated like a king. Now I know!!!!!

Probably my best stay ever.

I stayed at this hotel with my family at room 501. most of the time I was studying so I wouldn’t leave the room at all, because I had an important exam in Paris for my school. After two weeks of staying there, the day that I passed my exam, we decided to go out. We were out for about 6 hours and when we came back, I saw that the room was made and my Louis Vuitton backpack with all the stuff that was in it was missing. The person who stole it must have had the card to get into my room, other than that who else could have gone inside my room!!! But unfortunately the manager Myriam was really rude and not helpful at all. She didn’t find out who did this shameful thing. And now after 4 months of waiting for the hotel insurance still we did not get any money back. This place is super small. The rooms are super small. The staff are so mean especially the ones at the restaurant. They barely have food at their restaurant, room service is so bad. The manager never ever said sorry or apologizing for what they did to us. Please be careful with your stuff if you ever go to this hotel. The worst experience about Paris. We expected to get robbed outside but not from our own hotel room. It’s a shame.

From arriving to departure the staff were amazing, friendly and helpful. The food was good and spa lovely. The room was so quite considering where it was. House keeping was good and the room amazingly clean.

Only thing is a little more milk in the room although as there is a supermarket up the road you can easily buy extra milk.

Hi, my wife and I are, just wanted to let you know that we had a nice and relaxing time In you hotel.

All staff were very helpful and friendly, no rush and food was fantastic.
Room was amazing, nice surprise with the views of Boulevard Haussmann.
Pool and steam room was clean and very refreshing.

Also like to thank the staff for assisting me today with problems checking in on airline website.

Hotel is located really close to the city centre. 30 minutes walk to the arc de triumph.

A superb hotel.

The main purpose of the trip was business and thus the location chosen strategically as LVH was a mere 5-minute walk to the client's office. However, my wife accompanied me and we decided to stay a few extra days in Paris given this was the first time in France for the both of us. We couldn't be happier with the decision as LVH was central to a number of attractions and VERY walkable to many restaurants and shops.

From the start, service was impeccable. We had a late check-in but were completely blown away by the attentiveness of Nicolas, who was essentially the only person on site. In the following days, each and every one of the hotel employees went out of their way to make sure our needs were met.

Rooms are on the smaller side but that's really about the only downside. They were new, clean and comfortable. As an added bonus, the downstairs spa lounge (with pool and steam room) are a treat. We'd absolutely stay here again given the opportunity. Great job, keep it up!

Had a great time at the hotel, well situated, good facilities and great service (unusual in France). Specifically to mention Arnaud who has done above and beyond to make the stay pleasant. Would definitely come back!

I stayed at This hotel , thinking it should be a good hotel since it’s located in a good area. But don’t get fool. Their restaurant sucks, they don’t have a good food at all and one of the server who also checks mini bar, is such a crazy rude person. He’s always mean and angry. The manager Maryam is such a rude lady too. The pool is so small but when you look at the pictures, you would think that it’s wow, and most of the times it’s closed and they are repairing. The water had too much chemical and they had to close it. No wonder why my eyes were burning when I went to the pool. There are tons of other hotels on this area. Try to make sure you go somewhere much better with more polite people.

This was a one night stopover, with a late checkin. The pool was a relief in the morning, and the location very good for business and shopping. I had lunch in the restaurant which was also very good.

My room had good view down Blvd Hausmann, was clean, quite stylish with good bathroom and shower.

The staff were friendly, efficient and helpful.

Definitely a recommend.

While on a business trip I spent two nights in hotel La Villa Haussmann. The hotel is well located, not far from several metro stations (Miromesnil, lines 9 and 13) and a ten minute walk away from Gare Saint-Lazare.

Check-in was smooth, during which I was assigned room 203. This seemed to be a standard room, facing Boulevard Haussmann. Although the street my room faced is a busy road, I didn’t hear any traffic as they had double windows with double glazing, this was great. The room itself was nicely designed although somewhat small. The bathroom was small but functional and had a nice design as well. There was a small bathtub which also functioned as a shower cabin. The toilet was separate from the main bathroom. The bed was very comfortable and the WiFi reasonably fast and stable.

In the basement of the hotel (level -1) there is a gym (read workout room, very small and not a lot of equipment), a pool (very nice, water temperature around 38 degrees C) as well as a steam room (press the button just next to the entrance door of steam room and give it 15 minutes to heat up).

My experience is that French hotels are not world famous for their breakfast, and this hotel is no exception. Breakfast was not bad, but nothing special either. They served good espressos though.

What I liked:
-very comfortable bed
-nicely designed room
-extremely good soundproofing towards outside
-fast WiFi
-pool
-steam room

What I disliked/ points for improvement
-small room
-sink in bathroom was damaged
-vibrations from nearby metro line/ train line could be felt

All in all a good hotel in a very nice neighborhood of Paris.

Perfect service at a great location in the beautiful 8th arrondissement, a typical Parisien style architecture that is very appealing. Room service is super fast. Very friendly staff. Many thanks for the room upgrade!

This beautiful hotel is perfectly situated and very comfortable. Breakfast each morning is very nice. I love fresh orange juice. It does feel like the room service needs a tiny bit of polish. I had to ask for shampoo after using the same bottle for a week and finally running out. Sometimes water was put in my room and sometimes not. It’s the little things that make a big difference. Overall it was very nice.

ALL the staff were amazing, friendly and professional. This was the last stop on our honeymoon and when we told them they gave us a great room! The rooms are more modern and very clean. We loved the pool and sauna!! We went there nearly every night to unwind! When we come back to Paris, we will only stay at this hotel!

My partner and I stayed at the hotel in mid Sept 2018. We found the hotel to be very nice. The staff were always very curteous. The rooms are a little small, but that did not bother us as when you are in Paris you should only spend very little time in your room :) the breakfast was very nice although somewhat limited. The hotel is in a great location to explore Paris and the pool and spa area is excellent. I would recommend staying at this hotel.

We recently had 4 nights at La Villa Haussmann in Paris. The room size is small especially by Australian standards. It does have a separate toilet from the bathroom which was handy. The tea and coffee facilities are limited so be prepared to buy your own milk etc from one of the many convenience stores around. Having said all that the room is very comfortable and well appointed. The location is great from both the shopping district, about 10 minutes walk, and the Champs Elleyse which is a slightly longer walk at about 15 minutes. We had breakfast included and it was also good, The staff were very friendly. We didn’t experience any of the negative things that are said about the French. To the contrary, and we have travelled through The Netherlands and Germany on our trip the French were the friendliest. Overall highly recommend the La Villa Haussmann!

We had an exceptional experience during our stay at LVH. Our room was ready upon arrival at 10:30 am. The staff were fantastic. The hotel is located in a very elegant area and very safe for walking around late at night. The hotel appears to be new. We had the Deluxe room with a step out balcony over looking Haussmann Blvd. When the balcony door is closed you can not hear noise from the street. The room was spotless. Although the room was small, the layout was well organized (huge flat screen TV, bar, refrigerator, 2 large chairs, a bench, table, two night stands, king size bed and a large closet for 2 people). The bed was extremely comfortable. The decor of the room, the hotel and paintings throughout are beautiful. The bathroom was a nice size, the shower was wonderful, and there was a table with three shelves for whatever you wanted to use it for.
We highly recommend this hotel and will be back next year.

Pros -
Bed was very comfortable
TV good

Cons
The room smelled of sewer gas. Reported it. Read online to close sink and tub drains which appeared to solve the problem.
Restaurant staff were overworked. Not really a restaurant more of a lounge.
No real concierge only hotel staff that gave mixed recommendations.

Wouldn’t stay again.

Definitely not 5 stars.

For business trips a hotel has to provide some basic functions right first time to avoid being average.
At the daily rate charged I don’t expect to have to do running repairs on the shower heads (scaled up) and water taps (broken mechanisms).
Equally would be helpful to provide basic instructions beside non logical air con controls.
Not good enough I’m afraid even with great staff.

Nice hotel near St Augustin. Friendly staff. Rooms small but well laid out. Restaurant looked nice but I ate at a nearly Brasserie. Didn’t have breakfast as wasn’t included in rate. Would recommend as well centrally located.

Location: Very handy location. Easy to get around from. The station we used most was Miromesnil. With a transfer or so you can get about anywhere.

Staff: all staff were very friendly and provided top notch service. They were very personable and really showed an effort to assist at all times.

Room: room was nicely done but it is extremely small. I suppose that is expected in Paris but wanted to point it out. We had two mid sized suitcase and barely managed to find spots for them which took up any seating area available. Shower was great. Air conditioning was quiet. (I hate loud fans). We were able to sleep very well each night.

Amenities: we were out pretty much all the time and didn’t get to make use of the restaurant, gym or pool. However we did take a look at the gym and pool out of curiosity. And for those that work out. The gym is very small. It’s got two cardio machines and one set of adjustable dumbells. Again I’m not expecting a big gym or any gym in Paris hotels and I had zero time anyways. We did go for a jog outside one day so the gym is nice but not really expected or necessary.

Overall: Great hotel and I would stay there again.

I cannot say enough good about this hotel. It's small, but boy is it beautiful. A mix of classic Parisian style (white marble bathrooms and little balconies from the rooms). But it's also slightly Rococo, with it's mix of dark wood, marble floors and rich pinks, turquoise and green upholstery. The breakfast was excellent and the spa - true luxury. The only let down was that there didn't appear to be much on the menu for lunch or dinner. That said, the hotel is on one of the main shopping streets and there are many, many restaurants to eat in there.

The entrance for the hotel does not have a visible sign but the entrance to the restaurant is visible. The rooms are very small. It is about 220 square feet. Really just enough room for the bed. The rooms are decorated nicely. The bath tub is high so if you have range of motion problems this will not work for you. Location wise is not bad. The metro is 700 feet away, Eiffel Tower is 2.5 miles away. The coffee maker was dirty. Drinks from the lobby bar are weak, even the beer only comes in a 8 oz glass (not worth the cost). The night bar manager is very nice.

We were very excited about our upcoming stay at La Villa Haussman in Paris and were more than delighted with the hotel. The location was great, the rooms were quiet, and beds very comfortable. The staff was very friendly, courteous, and helpful. The pool was truly a treat. We decided to take it easy on our last day and couldn't have had a better experience. Biggest disappointment was checking out!

Hotel was amazing. Decor inside was lovely, the staff were very friendly and helpful and the spa area looks every bit as good as the pictures.
It’s also in a good location to walk to all the major attractions. Would highly recommend and would definitely stay again.

My wife and I had been in Paris before but this was our first time with our 3 year old daughter. Since it was a July we decided to look for a hotel that had a swimming pool. La Villa Haussmann was perfect for our needs. Location is great with easy access to the subway but we could walk to the Arc de Triumph and even the Eiffel Tower. Service was friendly , the room larger than usual for Paris with a large bathroom. The pool was great, we used it every day of our stay and most times had it for ourselves. Our daughter enjoyed it a lot but I was pleased to find that the pool also had an artificial tide so it was great for a hard workout as well. So after this experience La Villa Haussmann has been added to our list of “go to” hotels in Paris.

A great hotel with great service, very polite team with fully support in term of all aspects, the breakfast is diverse and delouses and the room are very comfortable. bathrooms very good with a lot of facilities, there are a gentleman called David and lady Called Maria oriented us for a lot of things Paris with very kind way to deal, and the hotel dealing with a agency to facilitate the booking for the most popular touristic places at Paris. hopefully I will back again to La Villa Haussmann.

We spent two wonderful nights in Paris. The hotel is centrally located to everything and every person we dealt with at the hotel was extremely helpful and friendly. Thanks La Villa Haussmann for a lovely stay. Absolutely perfect!

La Villa Haussmann was a mix of very good, okay, and very bad.

THE BAD: Some of the deluxe rooms.

We reserved a deluxe room (258 sq ft) and asked for a high floor, good view, and balcony. LVH delivered on exactly what we asked for...but we Hated the room. It’s impossible that that’s 258 square feet; there was about a foot of space on the two sides of the bed, and a foot more at the end of the bed...but there was a table there. There was a couple feet of space BEHIND the bed, and a shelf...but it was just insanely cramped. Maybe it’s 258 sq ft if you count the balcony...and the shower.

There is a lovely view out the window to the side of the bed. The window is actually an interior and exterior pair of tight-sealing large French doors. When those doors are closed, the room is incredibly silent. When opened...just kidding! You can’t open the doors to the side of the bed because they just hit the bed. There’s no way out onto the balcony. You also have to walk around the bed to get to the other door. You also can’t open the doors to the foot of the bed because the table is in the way. The room was a nightmare. (We got moved to another Deluxe room that was much better.)

THE BAD: The minibar.

One night, we put some food from a market in the minibar, which LVH was kind enough to empty out at our request. The next morning, we learned that the minibar is technically a cooler, not a refrigerator. If you have medication or buy something perishable, you need to find another solution for storing it safely. We asked, and none of the rooms have a device that will keep contents from spoiling. It’s for beverages only. We threw the food out.

THE BAD: The staff walking in on you.

On several occasions, we had someone knock and then walk right in despite “Just a minute!” and then more protestations as they barged on in. We’d seen this complaint in other reviews, and didn’t have to wait even an hour to experience it firsthand.

THE BAD: The not-downstairs staff

On our first evening, there was a knock at the door. I said “wait!” and ran to the door. As the gentleman opened the door anyway (third time so far), I was able to stand in the doorway so he couldn’t walk into the room. He said that he had bottled water for us. I said great! He asked if we already had two bottles of water. I said yes, because two were in the room when we arrived. He said “okay!” and started to move on. I said “Can we have two more?” He said “No.”

For all the reviews wondering why this isn’t a five-star hotel, “No” is a great example. My wife and I got a good laugh out of it. Where else are you going to get refused water?

I left the Do Not Disturb sign up permanently after that. As a result, every time we had to call downstairs--which was frequent--we had to remember to take the sign down.

THE BAD: Housekeeping

***This is the category that really costs LVH’s rating.***

On the first night, we discovered that there was a duvet, but no top sheet on the bed. We called downstairs, took the Do Not Disturb sign down and waited for someone to walk in, got the sheet, and put the DND sign back up.

The next morning, we discovered that there was no conditioner. I mistakenly expected housekeeping to notice that when they refreshed the room later that day. They didn’t. We called downstairs, took the DND sign down and waited for someone to walk in, got the conditioner, and put the DND sign back up.

We tend to drink (a lot of) decaf and had gotten some extra decaf Nespresso pods the first evening. We finished them the next morning, but they were replaced with only caffeinated pods. At a five-star hotel we stayed at in Rome (Grand Hotel Via Veneto), when they understood that we were big decaf fans, they gave us a tray with at least a dozen decaf pods on it. At LVH, they never caught on.

Also, when they refreshed the room on Day 2, they took but did not replace the mugs, bathrobes, or top sheet. We called and did the DND routine. I will say that the staff responded quickly and addressed the issues. So, the service was excellent, but only after it was shockingly lacking.

The next day, the towels were taken but not replaced. Call, DND, etc.

The next day, the conditioner was not replaced. Call, DND, etc.

The next day, the mugs and towels were not replaced. Call, DND, etc.

The next day, the top sheet was not replaced. I think that yielded our tenth housekeeping-problem call, which resulted in us being provided a second duvet cover instead of a sheet. I gave up at that point; it was our last night.

I’ve traveled a lot, and I’ve stayed in all levels of hotels. You’d never find housekeeping this poor in a $100-per-night Hampton Inn. If you did, they’d refund you your money. At $400 a night, this went past annoying and into the surreal.

THE MIXED: Some other deluxe rooms.

The Deluxe room we got moved into (301) was a huge improvement. You could actually open the French-door window, for starters. Not all the way, because it still hits the bed. But it could be what you would call “open.”

It also had a ton of closet space and shelves that let us move in and stow our suitcases. LVH actually offers a service where, once your suitcases are empty, they’ll store them downstairs for you until you’re ready to re-pack; they know the rooms are SMALL. But compared to the first room, 301 was a paradise. Needless to say, there’s no desk; this hotel is not recommended for business travelers. But the shelves made it perfectly livable for a romantic week in Paris.

The room has two chairs and a table that can fit two place settings but not much else, and the room is too small for a rolling room service tray--so we had to put the hand-carried room service tray on the bed. It worked, but we were constantly aware how small the room was. Again, this was the larger of the Deluxe rooms.

We slept surprisingly well. As in the nightmare room, the double window-doors seal out all noise.

The bed was pretty hard, but felt pretty close to true USA king width, and that matters a bit when one of you has the Jimmy legs.

The blackout curtains aren’t, quite. They leak enough light above and around them that you’ll wake up with the sun if you don’t bring a mask.

LVH does provide an electric kettle, and if you’re American and like big coffees, I strongly suggest bringing some instant or powdered coffee and making your own in the room. Bring your own mugs, too, because housekeeping won’t be replacing the ones you use.

THE MIXED: Room service

Room service our first night arrived pretty quickly, and the club sandwich was far better than I’d expected. Seriously, order the club sandwich!

On our last morning, our in-room breakfast (six euro surcharge per person--a steal on your check-out day) was pretty inaccurate. We indicated quantities on the order sheet but they didn’t see them. They also gave us caffeinated rather than decaf coffee. The hard boiled eggs varied from hard to soft to almost raw. We called and it got corrected very quickly, of course. But it was yet another call to address yet another issue.

THE GOOD: The location.

The location of this hotel really can’t be beat. It’s not especially close to any sights, but it’s a block from a large market (Monoprix), a block from a two-line metro station (Miromesnil), and a block from several restaurants and cafes. A pharmacy is literally next door. We went to Paris to stroll and feel what it’s like to be there. We found the 8th and 9th districts, up to Montmartre in the 18th, to be hands-down the best. (St Germain--the 6th--is nice as well, and it’s easy to access by metro or Uber from LVH.)

THE GOOD: The bathroom.

At least in 301, the shower has both a wand and a rainfall showerhead--and a tub. The toilet is in a separate room. There is another set of large French door-windows (frosted for privacy) that seal silently or can be opened into the bathroom. There’s plenty of room, and even a cabinet with shelves under the sink so you have room for all your stuff.

The toiletries--when housekeeping bothers to stock them--are fantastic. The shampoo, shower gel, and lotion are Heeley Cardinal. The conditioner is Replica Jazz Club. It’s a testament to the quality of the hotel when you want their products in your own home!

THE GOOD: The quiet.

Seriously, the seals on the French-door windows in the rooms are worth their own separate mention. If you want to guarantee that you will have a quiet night’s sleep, LVH should be high on your list.

And 301 was actually right next to the elevator, but we didn’t hear a single noise from it.

THE GOOD: The buffet breakfast.

Breakfast downstairs was excellent.

Christophe, Eman, and Maud were accommodating, kind, responsive, funny, and made us feel incredibly welcomed. Christophe was especially great.

The spread is entirely adequate, and the baked goods are especially tasty. They have a fantastic gluten-free chocolate cake, and a pound-cake-like loaf called quatre-quart that I fell in love with.

There is also a device that lets you soft/hard boil your own eggs to your liking. Pro tip: Turn it up to 100 a few minutes before starting the timer. I “boiled” eggs in 60-degree water my first day. That didn’t work--but that was my fault.

THE GOOD: The downstairs staff.

When we asked to be moved to a different room, the front-desk staff (Pauline and Megane) were incredibly gracious, and took care of everything quickly.

Despite all the problems we had, the downstairs crew was constantly doing their best to recover from the upstairs staff and housekeeping’s errors.

At checkout, Maud gave me a few slices of quatre-quart as a going-away present. That kind of thoughtful touch is a big part of why I’d consider staying here again. But the gulf between the quality of the folks downstairs and the folks barging into the room or forgetting to put sheets on the bed (!!!) is why LVH can’t possibly earn more than 3 out of 5 stars.

I feel a little bad posting this review precisely because the staff tried so hard to overcome all the issues we had. But I want to help other travelers know what to expect in their stay. If you want absolute silence at night in an upscale hotel in a great location, LVH is for you. If staff barging into your room, massive housekeeping issues, and a lack of space is going to be a problem for you, look somewhere else.

My wife and I visited Paris in the middle of the summer. The hotel is very nicely appointed and the staff is very helpful. Our room was small but had everything we needed (A/c, mini fridge, coffee) and the bed was super comfortable. The pool is amazing, there are jets that can give you a bubble massage while laying down. It's a magical spot. There are chairs to lay down and chill too.
Very centric location.
Marko

We stayed at La Villa Haussmann for 2 nights recently. Overall the stay was a mixed bag.

Good:

Location is nice, safe and quiet.

Megane checked us in, she was lovely, helpful and her English was excellent - much better than my French!

Good tech in the room - Bose Bluetooth speaker, big Samsung flat screen, Nespresso machine.

The pool area was a great feature and was a nice relaxing end to the day.

The welcome drink was a nice touch.

Not so good:

Whilst the pool area is a good feature, it doesn’t feel that well maintained. There are uplighters around the edge of the pool, 6 of which weren’t working. The metal strips at the edge of each run of tiles (there are lots) are all rusty and the ledge around the edge of the pool was dirty.

The room is small. Whilst the room sizes are outlined, ours was more of a layout issue. You cannot move around the room with another person sharing the room, you’ll be dodging each other and climbing over each other constantly.

At this price point I would expect a bath in the bathroom, not just a shower; especially in a ‘Deluxe’ room.

When we arrived the Nespresso pods hadn’t been restocked and there was sugar spilt in the tray - this obviously hadn’t been tended to by housekeeping.

The rooms have nice big windows but unfortunately the curtains that covered ours were almost impossible to move. They were so stiff, my girlfriend couldn’t move them on her own and it took me several attempts.

Lastly, on our first morning, the housekeeping lady unlocked and came into our room without knocking. This is completely unacceptable. I’m not sure if she thought the room was empty but rather than leave she kept asking to clean the bathroom - why couldn’t this wait until we had left? And more concerningly as we were getting ready, what if we weren’t fully clothed? It left us feeling intruded upon.

Overall Villa Haussmann is nice, but I feel a lack of attention to detail really affected our opinion of it. I think next time we are in Paris we will revert to our original hotel of choice.

My wife and I had booked an apartment using Airbnb and we found that it was somewhat lacking in its description so for the last week of our one month stay we searched for a hotel in the 8th Arrond of Paris and found VIlla Haussmann.

The hotel is well located in this district of the city that has a bit of a business feel to it, although the area still has a few boulangeries and in fact a wonderful wine store just down the street that has been around since about 1850.

The rooms were somewhat highly priced, however the hotel has a pool, albeit a modes sized one (about 20 feet - 6 or 7 meters in length) and has a nice wet sauna (Haman) .

The rooms were somewhat on the smaller size but comfortable and the bed was nice and pillows were adequate. The curtains cut out the sun when one wanted to sleep and the bathroom amenities were good, although there was not that much liquid soap supplied.

The location was good as we could walk about 25 minutes to get to the 1st Arrond and 20 min to rue St Honore to check out the local high end boutiques.

I did wonder though why the hotel did not make more effort to entice us to eat in the hotel. Perhaps this is something they could work on. All in al a comfortable place, quiet in the evening, relaxing with great customer services.

We had the pleasure of staying here last week. What an amazing place in Paris!

The incredible staff made us feel so welcome, we have 2 children and they added an extra bed in the room for us which helped as otherwise we might of had to book 2 x rooms and slept separately.

Great service!

The indoor pool and wellness area was the best we’ve seen in all hotels.

The Hammam was first class. It smelled of eucalyptus and was so perfect to refresh after an 8 hour day walking around Paris. The pool? How fantastic! It had these jets that made it hard to swim for resistance training, the spa had the perfect amount of bubbles and the twirly action in the water meant you could float. Just wave your hands by the blue lights for it to work!

It’s seriously a beautiful and luxurious hotel. Worth every $$$$$

I decided to show my friend Paris after she visited me from Australia in the UK as a surprise trip. Of course wanting things to be perfect I decided upon La Villa Haussmann as a hotel base. Our plans where thrown together at the last minute and anyhow we finally arrive there around 11am and I knew it would be a wait till we got our room.
After being greeted by a friendly front desk we where told our room was ready. Wow first treat and up to the room we went.
Everything clean and in nice order Rebecca was impressed and so was I
The hotel staff couldnt have been more helpfull with anything we asked of them.Extra towels, tea bags etc etc nothing seemed a problem, even booking a romantic meal reservation at a posh fish restaurant.
The hotel is in a good location, north of the river and central, but its so easy to get an Uber or taxi anywhere.
I really want to say this is a great Hotel with amazing staff, just fantastic.

My husband and I stayed here for our first trip to Paris and we were not disappointed! The rooms we super clean and modern and the whole vibe of the hotel was delightful. Hotel staff were very friendly and accommodating. One thing I really liked about this hotel was that the windows were very soundproof, so despite the very busy street outside, it felt calm & quiet inside of our room. The pool and sauna were amazing after a long day of walking around Paris. Centrally located to all major landmarks and shopping.

I like it at this hotel as the customer service was awesome from all members of staff that I interacted with.

The rooms are lovely but a bit small even with my upgrade to Deluxe Suite but Parisian Hotels are typically small.

This hotel has a restaurant on the property and the food was great.

The hotel is centrally located as I was able to walk to both Galeries Lafayette and Champs Elysees for shopping (15mins walk).

It is a small boutique hotel that is convenient and great.

This hotel is beautifully quirky. We stayed 5 nights in June and enjoyed every minute of it. Room was clean and compact, with a balcony overlooking the street. It's Location is perfectly close to public transportation and major shopping centers such as Printempts Haussman and Galeries Lafayette. The staffs were friendly and helpful. On the last day in Paris, we easily took a bus to Gare du Nord. Overall, it was a lovely stay.

Nothing wrong at this hotel. The staff was very friendly and helpful. Room was nice and clean.
Swimmingpool is a nice to have at your staying.
Hotel is close to metro but also very central to walk to your destinations.

We stayed for a week at villa haussmann and higjly enjoyed it. We stayed at suite 602 and everything was perfect and very nice. Highly recommend it. Not a very touristy area, nice and relaxed. Hotel is very nice and staff very nice as well.

When choosing a hotel in Paris is difficult since there are so many to chose from.

I researched a lot before choosing this one, and did I hit the bulls eye!

The location is great. About a mile from the Eiffel Tower and within walking distance of so many attractions. Well, location anyone can see it on a map, so enough about that.

The hotel itself is small and I would put it under the "Boutique Hotel" category. It has 43 rooms spread through 6 floors.

We reserved a Junior Suite and the room was great. Hotel rooms in Paris are smaller than anywhere else that I have ever visited, but this room had plenty of space for 3 people. The view was great, we could see the Eiffel Tower from it.

I have to say that the best thing about this hotel, the one thing that made our stay truly special, was the staff. When I booked the hotel I exchanged a lot of emails with them to set up airport transfer and a few other details. The response time was amazing (12 hours max) but usually only a couple hours.

Then when we arrived everyone was so friendly and nice. Stefano was great helping us set up a attractions "plan" so we wouldn't waste time in Paris. They also set up tickets for a few places like The Louvre, Bateaux Parisiens, etc. Every time we came back to the hotel we were greeted with smiles, it was really nice, it made us feel welcomed.
I have to thank Stefano, David, Pauline, Stéphane, and everyone else that helped make our time in Paris a wonderful experience.

Iron and ironing board is available upon request, and they can leave it in your room if you have something to press everyday.

The pool is amazing, to bad I didn't take my swimming attire to enjoy it.

This hotel is great, I highly recommend it.

I had the pleasure of staying at this hotel just for 2 days! The rooms are really nice and clean. They have awesome bathtubs (I love bathtubs!) They also have an incredible breakfast selection that is absolutely delicious! The spa is not bad either the pool is a great temperature and they keep it. Very clean!

I would definitely stay here again!

A fabulous base for exploring the delights of Paris. Close to a metro station, or a pretty easy walk to the "main sights" if that's what you'd prefer. The staff were delightful - friendly and helpful, and graciously put up with my stumbling French! The room was as you'd expect in Paris - on the small side! However, spotlessly clean and very comfortable. Lovely shower with good water pressure. Considering it is on a fairly major boulevard, the excellent double glazing provides a quiet space, and it was lovely to throw open the doors onto the little balcony in the morning, for a peaceful view across the plane trees. Would absolutely recommend.

We visited LVH for an easter trip as a couple. Having done the standard trip advisor search, we decided to stay at LVH. A greta choice for anyone visiting Paris. The hotel was of superior quality and the pool is a lovely touch for an afternoon relax! The location is really handy also. Being on boulevard Haussmann itself provides a central base for trips to the whole of Paris. We ate out every night but the restaurant menu looked very appetising. If I return to Paris, I wouldn't look any further.

Hotel is quaint, rooms are spacious and clean. The location is phenomenal. What this hotel is lacking is a service up to the standard and a poorly run restaurant. Food is decent but bistro quality (french fries and steak) which is a disappointment given the hotel’s quality. The food is also very expensive (28 euros for french fries). As to the staff friendliness: their are freindly as long as you are not demanding anything out if the ordinary. Room staff was rude, I had to tell the room service guy three times to leave while i was in the bathroom as he was insisting to check the minibar.
Other than that everything was fine. Might check into other hotel next time.

This hotel was top of the line nice. Our room was very clean and overall the hotel was very quiet. The staff was extremely helpful. It was located in a nice area within walking distance of several very good dining choices.

My wife and I stayed at La Villa Haussman for 2 nights. First, let’s get the negative out of the way as there was only one thing that impacted our stay. The fire alarm was triggered twice in 2 days. First time after midnight and the second time at 7am. Apparently the issue is that the smoke alarms in the rooms are too sensitive so when some clients have hot showers, the steam triggers the hotel fire alarm waking up the whole hotel. Not great when you come for 2 relaxing nights seeking calm and a good night sleep...and paying that kind of money.
However the rest of the stay was perfect. The facilities were good and the staff very nice and helpful.
We really enjoyed the central location and the bakery right across from the hotel where you can get great bread and pastries.
Close walk to the river, the metro, shopping and monuments, it is very convenient for tourists. Also, an easy location to grab a Uber or Taxi when needed with only a few minutes wait.

Great hotel. Rooms were superb and so quiet with ample sound proofing provided. Breakfast was excellent. The pool and steam room was so welcomed after walking the streets of Paris. Highly recommended and I will return.

This was one of the better hotels I stayed ... I am beginning to be addicted to smaller, boutique hotels which offer personalised service and greater privacy. Used to mass productions in Asia where you meet 400 people for breakfast, this is a hotel you want to wake up in and feel rested and happy, in solitude! Excellent service, great staff, a very good well-stocked breakfast, BVLGARI amenities, some wonderful views (go for the junior suite if possible).

Enjoyed our stay at Villa Haussmann. Just the right location in 25 minutes walking distance to all major sight seeing spots. Rooms are well equipped and very comfortable. After a busy day relax in the Spa of the hotel.

My Husband and I chose to stay at La Villa Haussmann Hotel for their Pool. They have an excellent pool and hot tub. The interior is absolutely beautiful. Our bedroom was very nice as well. The modern decor and style of the room was beautiful. We had a double door balcony with a beautiful view. The only negative aspect of the room was that it was a bit small, but that’s Paris, most rooms are small. The location of the hotel is perfect and not Too far away from the Metro. The hospitality was excellent, we were greeted and bid farewell by Stéphan. I would recommend this hotel for anyone coming to Paris.

Our five day stay was very good! This is a new hotel with very clean and quiet rooms! It is perfectly located on a Main Street Windows are well insulated and within walking distance to the Opera, shopping and restaurants. The hotel also has a restaurant and offers breakfast for an additional cost.
You may arrange a private airport pick up, for a reasonable charge. Car very quiet and clean and courteous driver.
The only thing negative I will say is that the bathtub is not suitable for a person with disabilities. Bathtub is very high and difficult to get in to shower.You may want to check if the hotel has walk-in showers.
The front office and cleaning staff are extremely accommodating and friendly and speak Italian and English.
In the restaurant there is a very young waiter extremely friendly and helpful!
Thank you for all your assistance folks!

After a long 26hr flight from Australia the staff couldn't have been more warm and welcoming on our arrival. We were quickly checked in and shown to our rooms. After hearing all rooms in Paris are tiny, I was pleasantly surprised by the room size which was ample for our overnight stay. The location was excellent and the restaurant served a glorious breakfast. I would not hesitate in recommending this hotel for your stay in Paris.

Our experience at La Villa Haussmann was perfect from start to finish. The reception staff were excellent and could not do enough to help us, making a reservation for a nearby restaurant and helping us with directions to the sights. We stayed for 2 nights in a superior room which was extremely comfortable, modern and nicely furnished.

We also had very good service in the bar where Johan recommended some excellent wines for us to try. The location,staff and decor of the hotel all add up to make for a perfect stay in central Paris. We will be back !
